dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar run out (Lee) 79 (119b 7x4 0x6 184m) SR: 66.38

dismissalComment.html: Full in length, on the off and middle, Tendulkar missed a paddle sweep and the ball ran to Lee at short fine leg region. There was a huge shout for lbw and Bucknor turned it down. Meanwhile, Tendulkar had reached almost the middle of the track and was sent back but couldn't beat Lee's direct hit. It caught everybody by surprise. Gilchrist was still appealing...

dismissalComment.html: Got him! Again Hayden comes down the pitch, once more Kartik adjusts his flight and length and Hayden is beaten a touch. He goes through with the shot anyway. dismissalText.commentary: Andrew Symonds b Singh 75 (84b 3x4 1x6 103m) SR: 89.28

dismissalComment.html: Got him! This is a huge, huge wicket for India at this stage. Symonds, perhaps mindful of the fact that a boundary had not been struck in a while, tries to improvise. Symonds goes to the leg side and shapes to cut. The ball pitches on middle and straightens a touch and once Symonds has missed it only one result is possible. The middle stump is pegged back and India have a big wicket as the pressure mounts in this tight finish

dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting st †Dhoni b Pathan 29 (33b 5x4 0x6 62m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: Big blow. Ponting is stumped. Full in length, slanting away from Ponting who leans forward to drive. The bat comes outside the line and the ball threads the bat and pad gap. Dhoni gathers and whips the bails off in flash. He appeals for a stumping chance and it is referred upstairs. Ponting had lunged forward while trying to drive and his back foot was on the crease. The line belongs to the umpire and he is out. Ponting stands there for a long time, unhappy at the verdict. I can't understand why he stood so long there. He was seen muttering and gesticulating even as he walked up the stairs to reach the dressing room. It was a decision made by the third umpire.  Anyway ... that's that.

commentTextItems.html: swing and a miss and it's all over. India have won by 8 runs! It's been a really tight finish and finally India have managed to win a game in this series.

commentPostTextItems.html: Mahendra Singh Dhoni will be a relieved man. It's his first win as ODI captain and has taken four games to come by.

The Man of the Match is Mahendra Singh Dhoni for his all-round performance with bat and behind the stumps. That's all we have for you from the live commentary team. See you at the next game. This is Anand Vasu, saying cheers and goodbye, signing off.

low full-toss on the stumps, driven at, only the single as the ball is dug out
short of a length, on the stumps, Lee has a huge swing and a miss, through to the keeper
fullish and on the stumps, driven to the off side, just the single this time

commentPreTextItems.html: 16 needed from 6 now. Zaheer Khan to bowl.

commentTextItems.html: Bang! That is a quality hit to begin the over from Hopes. The ball is full, straight and right in the slot. Hopes cashes in with a straight drive that races away to the fence
full and outside the off, squeezed through point and just another single. India won't mind that. Excellent over from RP in the context of the match

dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar run out (Lee) 79 (119b 7x4 0x6 184m) SR: 66.38

dismissalComment.html: Full in length, on the off and middle, Tendulkar missed a paddle sweep and the ball ran to Lee at short fine leg region. It caught everybody by surprise. Gilchrist was still appealing...

dismissalComment.html: Got him! Again Hayden comes down the pitch, once more Kartik adjusts his flight and length and Hayden is beaten a touch. He goes through with the shot anyway. dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting st †Dhoni b Pathan 29 (33b 5x4 0x6 62m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: Big blow. Ponting is stumped. Full in length, slanting away from Ponting who leans forward to drive. The bat comes outside the line and the ball threads the bat and pad gap. Dhoni gathers and whips the bails off in flash. He appeals for a stumping chance and it is referred upstairs. Ponting had lunged forward while trying to drive and his back foot was on the crease. The line belongs to the umpire and he is out. Ponting stands there for a long time, unhappy at the verdict. I can't understand why he stood so long there. He was seen muttering and gesticulating even as he walked up the stairs to reach the dressing room. It was a decision made by the third umpire.  Anyway ... that's that.

dismissalText.commentary: Andrew Symonds b Singh 75 (84b 3x4 1x6 103m) SR: 89.28

dismissalComment.html: Got him! This is a huge, huge wicket for India at this stage. Symonds, perhaps mindful of the fact that a boundary had not been struck in a while, tries to improvise. Symonds goes to the leg side and shapes to cut. The ball pitches on middle and straightens a touch and once Symonds has missed it only one result is possible. The middle stump is pegged back and India have a big wicket as the pressure mounts in this tight finish

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Hodge st †Dhoni b Harbhajan Singh 17 (29b 1x4 0x6 36m) SR: 58.62

The replay shows quite clearly that Hodge has dragged his foot out of the crease and he has to go as the third umpire gives the decision in India's favour
